modules.description: This module identifies and selects input and output formats for multimedia containers based on names, file extensions, or MIME types. It provides access to codec identifiers for audio, video, and subtitle streams within output formats. Use it to determine appropriate formats and codecs when reading from or writing to media files.

This module handles the full pipeline of demuxing and decoding for reading, and coding and muxing for writing multimedia containers. It identifies and selects input and output formats based on names, extensions, or MIME types, and provides access to codec identifiers for audio, video, and subtitle streams. You can use it to extract stream information from a media file, choose appropriate codecs for encoding, and write the resulting data to a new container. Specific operations include format detection, stream selection, and codec configuration for both reading and writing workflows.
